Reasoning: The paper deals with learning preferences for mobile manipulators, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The proposed coactive online learning framework involves machine learning techniques such as reinforcement learning and preference learning, which are part of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The regret bounds analysis and optimization of the learning algorithm involve concepts from machine learning theory (cs.LG). The paper also considers context-rich environments and human-robot interaction, which are relevant to human-computer interaction (cs.HC). Finally, the experimental evaluation involves computer vision techniques for object recognition and tracking, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV).
